                <Gloss>dependable</Gloss>
                <Gloss>reliable</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Since πιστός[b] is a type of passive derivative of πιστεύω[b], it may be necessary in a number of languages to render this passive relationship in an active form. For example, the phrase δοῦλε ἀγαθὲ καὶ πιστέ in {S:04002502100028} may be rendered as ‘good servant and one whom I can trust.’ In {S:05500201100002} the phrase πιστὸς ὁ λόγος may be rendered as ‘this is a saying we can have confidence in’ or ‘… that we can trust.’</Comments>
